    • Constructor Detail

      • SeSelector

        public SeSelector(SeProtocol seProtocol,
                  SeSelector.AtrFilter atrFilter,
                  SeSelector.AidSelector aidSelector,
                  java.lang.String extraInfo)
        Create a SeSelector to perform the SE selection

        if seProtocol is null, all protocols will match and the selection process will continue

        if seProtocol is not null, the current SE protocol will checked and the selection process will continue only if the protocol matches.

        if aidSelector is null, no 'select application' command is generated. In this case the SE must have a default application selected. (e.g. SAM or Rev1 Calypso cards)

        if aidSelector is not null, a 'select application' command is generated and performed. Furthermore, the status code is checked against the list of successful status codes in the SeSelector.AidSelector to determine if the SE matched or not the selection data.

        if atrFilter is null, no check of the ATR is performed. All SE will match.

        if atrFilter is not null, the ATR of the SE is compared with the regular expression provided in the SeSelector.AtrFilter in order to determine if the SE match or not the expected ATR.

        Parameters:
        seProtocol - the SE communication protocol
        atrFilter - the ATR filter
        aidSelector - the AID selection data
        extraInfo - information string (to be printed in logs)
